            <summary>What is the difference between DEG and RAD?</summary>
            <p>DEG (degrees) and RAD (radians) are two ways to measure angles. Degrees are more common in everyday use (a full circle = 360°). Radians are used in advanced mathematics and physics (a full circle = 2π radians).</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What does ANS mean?</summary>
            <p>ANS stores the last result so you can use it in the next calculation without retyping it.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is n! (factorial)?</summary>
            <p>The factorial of n is the product of all positive integers up to n. For example, 5! = 5×4×3×2×1 = 120. It is used in combinatorics and probability.</p>
